  My mind wanders back to those early years. At first wandering the East Commons destroying anything and everything that fell in my path. Slaying orcs by the scores with burning hatred that would not be sated. Man or beast it was all the same as they fell beneath my sword. I killed indiscriminately, with no remorse. My skills grew daily. Soon I was a very efficient killer. I took great pains to please my new Father,and he smiled on me with the gift of magic. This new tool was quickly added to my growing power.<br>
  I traveled farther and farther from Freeport in the seasons that followed. I ventured into the dungeons of Befallen to battle the undead. Traveled through Kithcor Forest to Highpass Hold where legions of orcs and gnolls met their doom by my hand. Exploring inside Highpass Keep it self to destroy the goblin infestation that dwells beneath its floors.<br>
  It was during my stay in Highkeep that I realized not all people feared my, or hated me for it. I came to know a young priest by the name of Linamar. He and I shared a battlefield one evening against a common foe,goblins. In an unfortunate turn of events our position was overrun by the dirty little creatures. Two of the group had fallen to the onslaught. The others in the party began to flee without warning. A pair of the foul creatures stood between me and the door. I had nearly finished one off when my lifeforce began to slip away. I gave up on any chance of leaving that place alive. Than in a sparkle of blue crystals my strength came back to me. I knew this was not Innoruuks hand saving me this time. I charged down the last goblin,and as my life would ebb out it would be renewed by the same magic time and again. Having dispatched the beast I turned to see Linamar still holding his position against the wall. He had stayed when warriors had ran. He had saved me when he could have saved himself. He knew what I was and who my lord was yet he did not scorn me for it. From that day on we fought side by side in many a battle. I had made a friend in a world where I did not think it was possible.<br>
